Copy = OGimg.copy()
lower = np.array([0,0,0])
higher = np.array([30,30,30])

mask = cv2.inRange(Copy, lower, higher)
inv_mask = cv2.bitwise_not(mask)
fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.imshow(inv_mask)
Out[4]:
<matplotlib.image.AxesImage at 0x1244aa03910>
In[5]:

cv2.drawContours(Copy, cont, -1, (0,255,0), 20)

c = max(cont, key=cv2.contourArea)
x,y,w,h = cv2.boundingRect(c)
img_new = OGimg[y:y+h, x:x+w]
